  "text": "To determine the relative contribution of each subtype of VGCC (L-, N-, P/Q-, R-, and T-types) to retrograde synaptic transmission, we used specific antagonists of each channel subtype. These antagonists do not exert postsynaptic effects on glutamatergic responses; therefore, any effect observed was anticipated to be presynaptic [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Of all the VGCC antagonists used, only the N-type blocker -conotoxin GVIA significantly reduced the ipRGC-mediated light-induced inward current of DACs (Fig. 8A) . Pooled data from rd1 and Cnga3",
